==Starting out==
===Inspecting the Goblin Generals===
* '''Player:''' Which one of these am I actually meant to be saving?
* '''Aris:''' Hmmm... neither of them were at the previous council meeting.
* '''Aris:''' The goblins get through leaders so fast I find it hard to keep track. I heard the last leader died during a game of pin the tail on the basilisk.
* '''Aris:''' Well, no worries. I'm sure if you just find something that they'll both eat then that should work. I hope.
* '''Player:''' Remembering the last time I dealt with these two, that may be easier said than done.
* '''Aris:''' Well you could try asking some of the other goblins in their village for ideas. You should be able to find it just to the North of Falador, unless they've decided the sky is the wrong colour there or something.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the cook===
* '''Player:''' Can we talk about what happened in the dining room?
* '''Cook:''' Wow! You were incredible! The way you defeated the Culinaromancer, you made it seem so easy!
* '''Player:''' So... I don't suppose you can remember how I defeated him can you?
* '''Cook:''' Of course! Which bit can't you remember doing?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Protecting the Dwarf}}
* {{topt|Protecting the Goblins}}
** '''Player:''' Those bickering goblins... How did I protect them again?
** '''Cook:''' Well, that was a weird one alright, you told me that they couldn't agree on what food they liked, so you ended up just mushing a bunch of stuff together somehow which seemed to do the trick.
** '''Player:''' Oh yeah... I remember now...
** '''Cook:''' Did you want a reminder on any other of your brave exploits?}}
** {{tact|previous}}
